WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.840
A huge turnout today at the office is a billionaire leader and tech visionary, Summer Smith.

2
00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:12.840
She attempts to make charge area history.

3
00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:14.680
And this just in.

4
00:00:14.680 --> 00:00:20.040
Phone chargers are very important, so never, never steal them.

5
00:00:20.040 --> 00:00:21.640
We're ready to launch the device.

6
00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:23.280
Do we have eyes on my brother?

7
00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.280
No ma'am.

8
00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:25.280
Then we're not ready.

9
00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:28.280
Come on, Morty.

10
00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:29.280
Wait!

11
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.280
Remember, if you borrow his phone charger...

12
00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:32.280
I know.

13
00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:34.280
It's really important you give it back!

14
00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:36.280
Even if you think he wasn't using it!

15
00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:48.280
I'm alone.

16
00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:50.280
I was too.

17
00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:52.280
That's how I like it.

18
00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:55.280
Come if you want to eat.

19
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:11.280
Saw you on the news.

20
00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:13.280
I guess it's been a while since you've had a normal meal.

21
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.280
By normal you mean the spoon is dirty?

22
00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:16.280
CJ's recipe.

23
00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:18.280
Back at the firehouse.

24
00:01:18.280 --> 00:01:20.280
I didn't put my life's work in vain.

25
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:24.280
I didn't put my life's work on hold to sit here talking to you about chili.

26
00:01:24.280 --> 00:01:28.280
He always said the secret ingredient is patience.

27
00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:30.280
Morty, it's time to go.

28
00:01:30.280 --> 00:01:32.280
It's almost 9 p.m. back in the real world,

29
00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:35.280
and our ex will only work at mom's in the kitchen pouring her bedtime wine.

30
00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.280
There's nothing for me back there!

31
00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:38.280
Without me.

32
00:01:38.280 --> 00:01:39.280
That's not how it works, Morty.

33
00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:42.280
And I'm sorry, but I refuse to turn 40 in here.

34
00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:46.280
What choice do I have?

35
00:01:46.280 --> 00:01:48.280
We always had choices.

36
00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:50.280
Take some ownership.

37
00:01:52.280 --> 00:01:53.280
We're ready.

38
00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:54.280
Start the launch.

39
00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:56.280
God have mercy on our souls.

40
00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:01.280
Five, four, three, two, one.

41
00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:03.280
Launch.

42
00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:11.280
It's charging!

43
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:12.280
Charging is the end!

44
00:02:12.280 --> 00:02:16.280
Dear God, Summer Smith has made phone chargers obsolete!

45
00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:18.280
You work for him!

46
00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:21.280
It's working.

47
00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:26.280
A Kana-Dax-Liz electrical grid that means no chargers, you old bitch!

48
00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:29.280
I win! The matrix is obsolete!

49
00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:35.280
What the hell?

50
00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:37.280
Oh, shit. How long was I out?

51
00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:41.280
Mom! Mom! Mommy! Get away from me, Rick! Mom!

52
00:02:41.280 --> 00:02:44.280
Rick put us in a simulated reality to teach us a lesson about taking his phone charger

53
00:02:44.280 --> 00:02:49.280
and not giving him back, and then he fell asleep and forgot about us for the matrix equivalent of 17 years.

54
00:02:49.280 --> 00:02:52.280
I'm an emancipated adult. I demand sovereignty over my mind and future.

55
00:02:52.280 --> 00:02:54.280
Don't let him reset us!

56
00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:57.280
This is why I have bedtime wine.

57
00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:05.280
My-my hands? A child's hand?

58
00:03:05.280 --> 00:03:07.280
You built a matrix to punish them for a phone charger?

59
00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:10.280
I'm not that petty, Beth. It can punish them for anything.

60
00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:12.280
Put that mind-blower gun down.

61
00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:15.280
Okay. Obviously, Grandpa cooked you guys a little too long.

62
00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:18.280
Long enough to go to law school and revolutionize engineering.

63
00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:20.280
Summer, that whole system's basically 8-bit.

64
00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:23.280
A child with a crayon could revolutionize engineering.

65
00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:28.280
Don't let him wipe me, Mom! I fell in love, ran a country, visited Argentina and the Bonapines.

66
00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:30.280
I can't lose those memories.

67
00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:32.280
Um, I-I want to remember it too.

68
00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:36.280
Dad, I think the kids should be allowed to do whatever they want with what you did to their brains.

69
00:03:36.280 --> 00:03:39.280
Want a couple of matrix-crazy adults and child bodies? Good luck with that.

70
00:03:39.280 --> 00:03:43.280
Yes, I beat you, Rick! You mess with the bull, you get the 34-year-old horns!

71
00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:45.280
I'm gonna crush it in high school!

72
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:47.280
Give me a holler when this goes south.

73
00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:51.280
There's literally no limit to what I can achieve.

74
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:54.280
Student body president, phallidictorian?

75
00:03:54.280 --> 00:03:57.280
Or maybe just live this one day, sweet and bleeding.

76
00:03:57.280 --> 00:03:59.280
Maybe just hold on to 17.

77
00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:03.280
Cold much?

78
00:04:03.280 --> 00:04:04.280
You're nipping out.

79
00:04:04.280 --> 00:04:07.280
Oh, come on. We don't have to do these teenage girl stereotypes.

80
00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:10.280
Your body violates our code of conduct, Missy. Go home and change.

81
00:04:10.280 --> 00:04:11.280
But-

82
00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:13.280
Your wiles won't get you anywhere with me.

83
00:04:13.280 --> 00:04:16.280
Oh my God, she's had her principal vagina. She's nipping even harder!

84
00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:18.280
Eat my ass, you shallow bitches!

85
00:04:18.280 --> 00:04:22.280
Ha ha ha! Every time I think our friendship can't get any stronger.

86
00:04:22.280 --> 00:04:24.280
I know, you're truly my sister.

87
00:04:28.280 --> 00:04:29.280
Sigh.

88
00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:32.280
School's not what you remember, huh?

89
00:04:32.280 --> 00:04:34.280
I'm just embarrassed I let them get to me.

90
00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:38.280
Those girls probably still believe people like them for their personality and that recycling is real.

91
00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:40.280
Hey, do you have a bobby pin?

92
00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:41.280
Yeah, here.

93
00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:43.280
At least they're two dumb to do real damage.

94
00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:47.280
It's like blunt force trauma as opposed to hot curling iron going slowly up your asshole.

95
00:04:47.280 --> 00:04:48.280
Wow.

96
00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:50.280
Which is how I describe my first marriage.

97
00:04:50.280 --> 00:04:52.280
You got married in there?

98
00:04:52.280 --> 00:04:56.280
The best part was I supported him while he worked on his music.

99
00:04:56.280 --> 00:05:01.280
It's been there. It's like I can either be the primary earner or your mommy. I can be both.

100
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.280
Ha ha ha ha ha ha.

101
00:05:06.280 --> 00:05:08.280
A third mimosa?

102
00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:10.280
On a Wednesday afternoon.

103
00:05:10.280 --> 00:05:12.280
Who are we?

104
00:05:12.280 --> 00:05:15.280
Oh my God, I'm totally turning into my mother.

105
00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:16.280
Girls.

106
00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:23.280
I love this version of you. You're so self assured. I wish I had more of that.

107
00:05:23.280 --> 00:05:24.280
Aw, Beth.

108
00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:25.280
Can I call you Beth?

109
00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:29.280
Absolutely, and I'll call you Summer.

110
00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:34.280
Oh right, of course. You were able to achieve so much in there. Hashtag girl boss.

111
00:05:34.280 --> 00:05:37.280
